Setting `editor.detectIndentation` as well as Command Palette command "Detect Indentation from Content" fails to work on 3 and 5 space indented C files. 

Example:
```c
int main(void) {
   int i;
   for (i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
      printf("%d\n", i);
   }
}
```
Here indent size is incorrectly set to 4 when it should be 3.

Example:
```c
int f(int x)
{
   if (10 <= x && x <= 20)
      return x;
   else
      return -x;
}
```
Here indent size is incorrectly set to 6 when it should be 3.

Example:
```c
#include <stdio.h>

int f(int x)
{
     if (10 <= x && x <= 20)
          return x;
     else
          return -x;
}

int main(void) {
     int i;
     for (i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
          printf("%d\n", f(i));
     }
     return 0;
}
```
Here indent size is incorrectly set to 4 when it should be 5.

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Open new file
2. Set Language Mode to C
3. Paste one of the code snippets
4. Run Command Palette command "Detect Indentation from Content"

<!-- Launch with `code --disable-extensions` to check. -->
Reproduces without extensions: Yes

